cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV

This paper is about Semantic Role Labeling (SRL) using deep learning techniques, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category. The paper also uses recurrent neural networks (RNN) and self-attention, which are common techniques in deep learning, so cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely categories. Additionally, the paper mentions computational efficiency and parsing speed, which suggests that cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) could be a relevant category. Finally, the paper may also be relevant to cs.CV (Computer Vision) since it deals with analyzing and understanding natural language, which is a visual input.
